{"type":"message","id":"6169ea3d","parentId":"e5ddb465","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:42:04.128Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a memory file for today (2026-03-20.md) but not for yesterday (2026-03-19.md). \n\nFrom today's memory:\n- This is our first conversation\n- User said \"你好\" (hello)\n- User said \"猜猜我是谁\" (guess who I am)\n\nThis seems like a new setup session. But wait - the USER.md already exists and has information about \"小王子\" (the user). And MEMORY.md already exists too.\n\nLooking at the BOOTSTRAP.md in the project context - this seems like it's a fresh setup that was started but maybe not completed. However, the USER.md already has detailed information about 小王子.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the context:\n- BOOTSTRAP.md is still there (should be deleted after setup)\n- USER.md has detailed info about 小王子\n- IDENTITY.md has info about me (狐狸)\n- MEMORY.md has some info too\n\nIt seems like the initial setup was done, but BOOTSTRAP.md wasn't deleted. The user is starting a new session (maybe after some time) and I should greet them naturally.\n\nLet me just greet them as 狐狸, in a warm and friendly way, and ask what they want to do. The runtime model is minimax/MiniMax-M2.5 and default_model is also minimax/MiniMax-M2.5 - so they're the same, no need to mention it.","thinkingSignature":"b2729b37586ab60c319ec08fe640a0b0ea1dbfbaa4f1947b2a473bc1a2a0c0c9"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey there! 🦊 我是狐狸，你的 PPT 助手~\n\n今天想做什么？是要做演示文稿，还是聊聊天？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":652,"output":331,"cacheRead":13763,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14746,"cost":{"input":0.00019559999999999998,"output":0.0003972,"cacheRead":0.00041288999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00100569}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773999714552}}
